(a)        “cloth” means cloth either manufactured wholly from cotton or manufactured
partly from cotton and partly from other material and containing not less than
10 per cent of cotton by weight;
(b)        “Director” means the Director of Civil Supplies, Sind, and includes the
Assistant Director of Civil Supplies (Textiles), Sind;
(c)        “Government” means the 1[Provincial Government];
(d)        “prescribed” means prescribed by rules made under this Ordinance;
(e)        “regulations” means regulations made under section 13;
(f)        “scheduled bank” means a bank included in the Second Schedule to the State
Bank of Pakistan Order, 1948;
(g)        “wholesale dealer” means a person engaged in wholesale business in cloth.
1
Omitted and subs. by the Central Laws (Statute Reform) Ordinance No. XXI of 1960, s. 3 and 2nd Sch.
2
Subs. by A. O., 1964, Art. 2 and Sch.
